  "A heart pacemaker uses an RC circuit to time its pulses. If the capacitor must reach 75% of the supply voltage before triggering, and tau = 1.2 s, at what time does the trigger occur?": "",
  "1.2 s": "",
  "2.4 s": "",
  "1.66 s": "",
  "0.83 s": "",
  "V/V0 = 0.75 = 1 - e^(-t/tau). So e^(-t/tau) = 0.25, giving -t/tau = ln(0.25) = -1.386. Therefore t = 1.386 * 1.2 = 1.66 s.": "",
  "Two RC circuits have the same capacitor (C = 50 microfarads) but different resistors: Circuit A has R = 1 k-ohm and Circuit B has R = 10 k-ohm. Both charge from the same battery. After one time constant of Circuit A, what fraction of maximum charge has Circuit B reached?": "",
