  "36.8%": "",
  "50%": "",
  "63.2%": "",
  "tau_A = 1000 * 50e-6 = 0.05 s. tau_B = 10000 * 50e-6 = 0.5 s. At t = 0.05 s, Circuit B has charged to 1 - e^(-0.05/0.5) = 1 - e^(-0.1) = 1 - 0.905 = 0.095 = 9.5%.": "",
  "A sensor circuit uses an RC network where the capacitor charges to 8 V (from a 12 V supply) and triggers an alarm. If R = 220 k-ohm and C = 4.7 microfarads, how long after the switch closes does the alarm trigger?": "",
  "0.52 s": "",
  "1.14 s": "",
  "2.06 s": "",
  "1.03 s": "",
  "tau = RC = 220000 * 4.7e-6 = 1.034 s. At trigger: 8 = 12(1 - e^(-t/1.034)), so e^(-t/1.034) = 1/3, giving t = 1.034 * ln(3) = 1.034 * 1.099 = 1.14 s.": ""
